body.name: KEEN Women's Nxis Speed Low Height Vented Hiking Shoes
features: Origin Made in the USA or Imported

TRACTION: KEEN.ALL-TERRAIN rubber outsole provides high-traction grip in muddy environments and on rocky surfaces; 4mm multi-direction lugs provide optimal grip for sure footing in the most rugged terrain
BREATHABILITY: Performance mesh upper with overlays and breathable textile lining provide lightweight durability while keeping your feet cool in warm conditions
FIT & DESIGN: Speed-lace webbing system with top collar hooks for comfortably snug fit; Original Fit–Iconic KEEN fit with generous space across forefoot for toes to spread out
SUPPORT & COMFORT: Removable PU insole for long-lasting comfort; Compression-molded EVA midsole for cushioning; Ergonomic toe notch provides added dexterity for better balance
CARE TIPS: Gently brush the footwear with a soft, damp sponge to remove loose dirt and restore surface; Stains should be treated immediately with a gentle cleaner
body.description: Speed hiking isn’t about going fast. It’s about experiencing more things. The terrain encountered is more varied – asphalt to trail to stream to stone steps. So we took the room-for-your-toes comfort, protection, and stability of our iconic hiker and gave it a running shoe feel. The NXIS Speed hiking shoes for women are built off KEEN's traditional wider footwear form. KEEN products are consciously created using PFC-free water repellent (in applicable styles) and leather sourced from Leather Working Group (LWG)-certified tanneries. KEEN makes shoes to make a difference. As a brand born for life outside, KEEN has a responsibility to protect and conserve the places where all people live, play and work with no ceiling. KEEN is committed to ensuring our products are free from manufacturing and material defects for one full year from the day you buy it from an authorized KEEN reseller. Some limitations apply. For details, be sure to carefully read the terms and conditions of KEEN’s warranty policy.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 23, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Wide Toe Box & Great Comfort
reviews.reviewText: Finally, a sneaker shoe with a toe box that doesn't make my toes cramp. The support is wonderful and the shoe looks good too. I use these for everyday walking around, not as a sport shoe.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 11, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Excellent lightweight quality hiking shoe
reviews.reviewText: This was my third attempt at buying a hiking shoe. I was prepared to be disappointed as I had been with the previous two purchases. Boy was I wrong. These Keen hiking shoes are comfortable right out of the box. These shoes are lightweight, stable and the quality is bar none. I am 60 years old and need a quality, comfortable, lightweight hiking shoe that is stable and wow they fit the bill perfectly. I highly recommend these hiking shoes!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 20, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Best Sneakers Ever
reviews.reviewText: I bought these sneakers a few months back specifically for a Fall trip to Europe. I live in the South and had been living in my multiple Keens sandals but needed something for warmer weather and maybe more walking. I say maybe because my sandals are amazing and I could probably use them if it was Summer even though they're not "technically" made for walking or hiking. I digress. So, I bought these right before my trip and wore them maybe once or twice for a short amount of time to "break in". Short story - I wore them through miles and miles of walking - including the hills of Lisbon! - through hours & hours (and more hours) of plane travel and they felt amazing the whole way. When I took a trip like this last year - before I discovered Keens - I ended up with blisters by day 3. Not anymore! Last but not least - they are SO cute! I love the color, style, heel all of it. Keens are just the best shoes and since I've discovered them I have only bought more styles and varieties. I'm just waiting for a nice work heel and I will buy only Keens forever!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars These hikers are a keeper!
reviews.reviewText: I buy Keen shoes because of their wide toebox. I have a bunion on each foot so finding comfortable shoes can be a chore. I own the Keen Voyageur and the Keen Targhee shoes, but I wanted to find a lighter-weight shoe. These shoes are fantastic! The mesh on the side aligns with my bunions which reduces the pressure on them. They have an insert that supports my arches and keeps my foot stable while walking. They look more like sneakers than hiking shoes and are very nice looking. I own another pair of mesh sneakers, but they do not protect my feet in the woods. I have worn them for several days on flat surfaces and so far so good. I love that they are breathable for the summer. I'm really pleased with these shoes.Update:I just returned from a 10-day vacation in Yellowstone National Park. I wore these shoes every day and am happy to report that I did not get a single blister. Not only did these shoes make walking on the many surfaces throughout my travels safe, my feet never felt sore or achy. These shoes are wonderful!
